  "prompt": "Do car manufacturers produce new models every year?",
  "response": "Car manufacturers typically release updated models for many vehicles on an annual basis, though this doesn't always mean creating entirely new models from scratch each year. Instead, a manufacturer may introduce:\n\n1. **Facelifts or Refreshes**: These can include minor cosmetic changes, updated features, or improved technology to keep a model competitive without a full redesign.\n\n2. **Full Redesigns**: These occur less frequently, often every 5 to 7 years, depending on the vehicle and manufacturer. A full redesign means significant changes to the model's design, architecture, and features.\n\n3. **New Trims or Variants**: Manufacturers may introduce new trim levels or special editions to keep a model fresh and offer more choices to consumers.\n\n4. **New Models**: Occasionally, manufacturers introduce entirely new model lines to address market demand for specific types of vehicles, such as electric vehicles, SUVs, or crossovers.\n\n5. **Phase-Outs**: Some models are discontinued if they are no longer popular or if a manufacturer shifts focus to other segments.\n\nThus, while manufacturers often release something new each year, it isn't always a completely new model.",
